## 7. Item catalog (reference)

### 7.1 The Blessing of Shieldon

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Domain | Exploration (meta-item) |
| Lifecycle | Single-use → consumed |
| Passive | +10% SPD |
| Skill | **Single use.** Enchant the `Possession` tag onto a target wonder item in your inventory. The Blessing is then consumed. Cannot target `Eternal` items. |
| CD | — (single use) |
| Tags | — |

### 7.2 THE VOID

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Domain | Hybrid (exploration passive, combat skill) |
| Lifecycle | Static (permanent burden) |
| Passive | **`Eternal` `Possession`.** Every 4 days, a **VOID PHANTOM** spawns on the overworld map. The player's vision is shared by all phantoms — they see what you see. Each time the player challenges a new node, all phantoms move one step toward the player's position. |
| Skill | **Combat only.** All foes lose their vision for 10 seconds. |
| CD | 2 days (day-based) |
| Tags | `Possession`, `Eternal` |

> **Design note:** THE VOID is a cursed item — once acquired, it cannot be removed.
> The phantoms create escalating map pressure: the more you explore, the closer they get.
> When a phantom reaches the player's position, it triggers a **BOSS fight** at that node.
> (Phantom contact mechanics are deferred to a future content pass — the spawning and
> movement rules are kept as placeholders.)

### 7.3 DD

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Domain | Hybrid |
| Lifecycle | Static |
| Passive | Each time you pick up a wonder core, heal 2% of max HP. |
| Skill | **Combat.** Release DD — a small bug-like creature that **crouches** on the ground. DD moves along the ground, devouring everything damageable in its path for **200 damage**. It turns around on hitting a wall. The player must **reclaim** DD (walk into it) to stow it again. |
| CD | 2 days (day-based) |
| Tags | — |

> **Design note:** The game does not pause when a combat node's goal is achieved or
> the timer expires — DD can still be reclaimed during the post-combat window. If the
> player leaves the node without reclaiming DD, it is **set free** (lost permanently).
> The item is removed from inventory. Don't forget to claim it back.

