| Passive | On a **melee attack hit**: bounce back **50% of post-mitigation damage** dealt to the target (thorns/reflect). |
| Skill | **Combat.** Knock back all enemies within 4 m. Deals **10 damage**. |
| CD | 15 s (second-based) |
| Tags | — |

### 7.11 QiongFeng Emperor of LOONG's Claw

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Domain | Exploration |
| Lifecycle | Conditional trigger → consumed |
| Passive | When the player **defeats the current world's LV4 boss**: immediately loot all **unopened chests** in that domain. After looting, the domain **cracks down** (becomes inaccessible). The claw then **faints** (is removed from inventory), and the player is teleported to a random valid location. |
| Skill | — |
| CD | — |
| Tags | — (consumed on trigger) |

> **Design note:** "Chests" and "domain" are future content. For now, "domain" = the
> current outer world, and "unopened chests" = combat/function nodes the player
> skipped. The world-crack is a dramatic irreversible action — use wisely. "Random valid
> location" must be selected deterministically from an explicitly-defined eligible-node set
> before implementation.

### 7.12 TwistedReality

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Domain | Hybrid (possession recovery passive, exploration skill) |
| Lifecycle | Static, unique boss reward |
| Passive | **`Possession`.** If the player suffers a terminal failure during a BOSS adventure, TwistedReality vanishes and returns the run to the start-of-day snapshot from the most recently completed day. The restored state is then stripped of TwistedReality; it cannot be used twice. |
| Skill | **Bridge of Eidolon — map only.** While held at a completed **Void-River peripheral city**, create an Eidolon bridge to the nearest eligible city in the closest realm. Neither endpoint may be devoured or already bridge-anchored. A bridge made from an LV4 capital instead targets the geometrically closest available LV5 city in zone 6. Every bridge has an **Eidolon Shelter** at its midpoint. The Shelter provides only Rest, Sharpen Weapon, Sharpen Armor, and Team Build; spending its Blessing immediately transfers the player to the opposite endpoint. |
| CD | **4 days** (day-based). Starts ready when acquired; no valid destination means no activation and no cooldown. |
| Tags | `Possession` |
| Acquisition | Guaranteed first-success reward for the starting realm's LV4 boss (`MapGDD.md` §5). |

> **Design note:** "Last day" is the complete state captured at the start of the current day:
> immediately after the preceding successful day-end resolution (or the fresh-run state on day
> 1). Boss KO and fatal BOSS timer expiry both qualify as terminal BOSS failures. TwistedReality's
> Possession passive therefore works from the backpack, while its bridge skill still requires the
> item to be held. The bridge does not consume stamina; its map-changing cost is the four-day
> cooldown and the irreversible route decision. See `MapGDD.md` §§5–7 and `NODES.gdd` §5.

### 7.13 A Weird Mushroom

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Domain | Hybrid |
| Lifecycle | Perishable → Convertible, OR Single-use → random outcome |
| Passive | **`Perishable` (2 days).** If not used within 2 days, converts to **A Rotten Mushroom**. |
| Skill | **Single use.** Increase max HP and current HP by **20%** (eater-only, permanent — a +20 pp max-HP multiplier). **The next day** (from start to end of that day), one random effect occurs. The player does **not** know the outcome before eating — the effect is revealed the following day. |

| Outcome | Probability | Effect (lasts the entire next day unless stated otherwise) |
|---------|------------|--------|
| (a) | 18% | Max-HP multiplier **−40 pp for that day** (net −20% vs the original base while active; current HP clamps ratio-preserved; restored at the next day-end) |
| (b) | 18% | Left/right movement controls swap for one day |
| (c) | 18% | Movement speed +300% for one day |
| (d) | 18% | Jump height +300% for one day |
| (e) | 18% | Gain an extra 20% HP (stacks with the initial +20%; permanent) |
| (f) | 10% | The protagonist who ate it can carry **one extra wonder item** (held slot +1, permanent) |

> All mushroom effects — the initial +20% and every outcome — apply to the **eater
> only**. Outcomes (b)/(c)/(d) last the entire next day and are intended at full
> strength: **+300% really means ×4** — this is a maniac item by design.

| CD | — (single use) |
| Tags | `Perishable`, `Convertible` |

### 7.14 A Rotten Mushroom

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Domain | Exploration (plantable) |
| Lifecycle | Plantable → harvest |
| Passive | — |
| Skill | — |
| CD | — |
| Tags | `Plantable` |
| Harvest time | 4 days |
| Fruit | 4× **A Weird Mushroom**. Each fruit inherits the father's max-HP modifier in the range **60%–140%**. Unlike the wild mushroom, each fruit has a **clearly labeled consequence** (a–f) visible before eating — the consequence is an **inheritable trait** determined at harvest time, rolled independently per fruit. |

