## 9. Decisions log

- **Two cooldown types.** Day-based CDs for world-map skills, second-based CDs for
  combat skills. An item may conceptually have both if it gains a second skill later.
- **Backpack is inert.** No passive, no CD tick, no skill access. This prevents the
  player from hoarding items for their passives and forces build decisions.
- **Possession is the exception to backpack inertness.** It decouples "where the item
  lives" from "whether the passive works." THE VOID uses this to be a permanent burden.
- **Benched protagonist → held item auto-returns to backpack.** Team build can only
  be changed at a shelter; the player cannot bench someone mid-combat to shuffle items.
- **Perishable ticks regardless of location.** A perishable item in the backpack still
  rots. The player can't "freeze" a mushroom by unequipping it.
- **Eternal is a strictly negative tag.** It locks the item into inventory forever and
  resists all modification, trading, and conversion. `Eternal` and `Convertible` are
  mutually exclusive.
- **Plantable items are consumed on planting.** They leave the inventory and become
  a world entity at the shelter. Harvest produces new items into inventory.
- **Convertible items preserve slot position.** If a held item converts, the successor
  stays held. Same for backpack.
- **Inheritance uses percentage ranges of the father's attributes** (e.g., 60%–140%
  of the HP bonus). Exact roll is determined at harvest time. Wild mushroom fruit each
  get a clearly labeled inheritable trait so the player knows what they're getting.
- **"Domain" = world.** QiongFeng claw's "domain" is the current outer world (one of
  the 5 world-fans on the map). "Domain boss" = the world's LV4 boss.
- **DD is a bug that crouches.** It must be reclaimed before leaving the node or it's
  set free and lost. The game does not pause on combat end — the reclaim window is real-time.
- **Pixolotl's Feather time-rewind scope is TBD.** The exact undo semantics need
  precise specification — particularly whether the day counter and VOID devour are
  affected. Safest default: position/HP/stamina revert; the clock does not.
- **Day-end resolution** (replacing "liquidation"): the moment when "Finish the Day"
  is confirmed, triggering cooldown ticks, perish-countdown ticks, and the VOID
  devour clock. This is the game's daily housekeeping pass.
- **VOID Phantom contact = BOSS fight.** Deferred to a future content pass; the
  spawning/movement rules are placeholders.
- **(v0.3.7) Possession is party-scope:** the passive applies to all protagonists in
  the active build (applied once — never doubled on the holder).
- **(v0.3.7) Mushroom semantics pinned:** all effects are eater-only; the initial +20%
  is a permanent +20 pp max-HP multiplier; outcome (a) is a one-day −40 pp max-HP
  debuff (net −20% vs original that day); (c)/(d) really are ×4 — maniac by design.
- **(v0.3.7) Permanent stat pools are additive** (max-HP percentage points, flat ATK,
  flat DEF) — see `30-DATA-AND-BALANCE.md` §3 and `NODES.gdd` §5.5.
- **(v0.6.0) Pome's Seed harvest revised to match the inheritance model.** Was 4 days /
  independently-randomized fruit; the harvest became **7 days / 60%–140% inheritance** of
  the father's rolled stats. The v0.10.0 design sync supersedes the previously specified fruit
  type and quantity, but preserves that 7-day inheritance rule. This also resolves a
  pre-existing conflict with `T30-FEATURE-BLUEPRINTS.md` §4, whose `ItemInstance.RolledStats`
  comment already assumed a "60–140% rolls" inheritance model project-wide.
- **(v0.10.0) TwistedReality is a possession recovery key and an Eidolon bridge-maker.** The
  first starting-realm LV4 victory awards it ready. Any terminal BOSS failure spends it to restore
  the last completed-day snapshot, even from the backpack. Held use builds an Eidolon Shelter at
  the bridge midpoint; its 4-day cooldown gates further bridges. An LV4-origin bridge is the only
  route into zone 6, so losing TwistedReality before creating one can strand the run outside.
- **(v0.10.0 design sync) Status extensions are duration, not stack, modifiers.** Pome's
  Bravery / Seed add 0.2 s to every OnFire application; FanChen's Heart does the same for
  Frozen. This intentionally requires a duration-capable status representation before those
  effects are implemented.
- **(v0.10.0 design sync) Yukai's Rope reaches 20 m.** The prior 80 m value was superseded;
  the first obstacle ends the rope and becomes the drag point.
- **(v0.10.0 design sync) The Claw is consumed, not converted.** Boss victory loots and
  cracks its domain, then teleports the player to a deterministic random valid location. The
  eligible-location rule remains a pre-implementation TBD.
- **(v0.10.0 design sync) Pome's Seed's harvest contents are TBD.** The confirmed rule is a
  7-day harvest whose inheritable attributes roll at 60%–140% of the father's values; the
  specific fruit type and quantity must be set before plantation work begins.
- **(v0.10.0 design sync) `Pixolotl` is the canonical spelling.** The catalog id and successor
  remain `pixolotls_wish`; the "Poxilotl" spelling in an early item list is treated as a typo.
